              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Thickness of t-target for 2MeV protons = 100keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "94-PU-239",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9697
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 880 ug/cm2 Pu-239 foil,",
                " purity=96.97%, active area=3 cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".of fission fragments and LCP.",
                "The natural alphas and fission fragments were stopped",
                "in an Al foil before reaching the LCP-detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PHD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".on the fission side,cutoff energy = approx 6MeV,",
                "on the LCP-side, cut-off energy = 8MeV.",
                "Before and after each fast-neutron run, thermal runs",
                "were performed to check the detector performance and",
                "for normalization of the LCP-spectra."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Filled with high purity argon,pressure = 1atm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Surface-barrier,diameter=2cm,depletion depth=",
                "400micro-m,mounted inside the ionization chamber, to",
                "detect light charged particles ('LCP').",
                "A low intensity Ac-227 source was used for energy",
                "calibration."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A Gaussian was fitted by least squares method to the",
                "measured spectra beyond 12MeV. The LCP-yields above",
                "12MeV were attributed to alpha-particles alone. The",
                "difference between measured spectra between 8 and 12MeV",
                "and Gaussian was assumed to be due to tritons. The",
                "quoted alpha and triton yields -relative to thermal-",
                "were obtained through this assumption."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The observed spectra were corrected for chance coinc.",
                "Using singles LCP-spectra, then for energy losses in",
                "the source, gas and Al foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
